ties''\n*[[Todd Orlando]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''Defensive Coordinator/Linebackers''\n*Darek Warehime&nbsp;\u2013 ''Special Teams Coordinator/Tight Ends''\n*Jason Washington&nbsp;\u2013 ''Recruiting Coordinator/Cornerbacks''\n*Yancy McKnight&nbsp;\u2013 ''Strength and Conditioning''\n}}\n\n==Game summaries==\n===vs Maryland===\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road=No. 23 Longhorns\n|R1=7\n|R2=15\n|R3=7\n|R4=0\n|Home='''Terrapins'''\n|H1=14\n|H2=10\n|H3=0\n|H4=10\n}}\n{{see also|2018 Maryland Terrapins football team}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Overall record\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Last meeting\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Result\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 3\u20131\n| 2017\n| UMD, 51\u201341\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===Tulsa===\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road=Golden Hurricane\n|R1=0\n|R2=0\n|R3=7\n|R4=14\n|Home='''Longhorns'''\n|H1=14\n|H2=7\n|H3=0\n|H4=7\n}}\n{{see also|2018 Tulsa Golden Hurricane football team}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Texas Longhorns|Overall record|Last meeting|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| colspan=3| ''First meeting''\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===USC===\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road=No. 22 Trojans\n|R1=14\n|R2=0\n|R3=0\n|R4=0\n|Home='''Longhorns'''\n|H1=3\n|H2=13\n|H3=21\n|H4=0\n}}\n{{see also|2018 USC Trojans football team}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Texas Longhorns|Overall record|Last meeting|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 1\u20135\n| 2017\n| USC, 27\u201324\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===TCU===\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road=No. 17 Horned Frogs\n|R1=6\n|R2=7\n|R3=3\n|R4=0\n|Home='''Longhorns'''\n|H1=7\n|H2=3\n|H3=14\n|H4=7\n}}\n{{see also|2018 TCU Horned Frogs football team|TCU\u2013Texas football rivalry}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Texas Longhorns|Overall record|Last meeting|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 62\u201325\u20131\n| 2017\n| TCU, 24\u20137\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===at Kansas State===\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road='''No. 18 Longhorns'''\n|R1=7\n|R2=12\n|R3=0\n|R4=0\n|Home=Wildcats\n|H1=0\n|H2=0\n|H3=7\n|H4=7\n}}\n{{see also|2018 Kansas State Wildcats football team}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Overall record\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Last meeting\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Result\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 8\u201310\n| 2017\n| TEX, 40\u201334\n|}\n{{-}}\nTexas lost their first game on the road at Maryland and then won their next three games at home, and their last two victories came against ranked teams\u2014No. 22 Southern California and No. 17 TCU.  But the travel games (especially in this series) have not been in the Longhorn's favor.  The home team has won last six games between the two teams and Texas has not won in Manhattan since 2002.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/college-football/preview?gameId=401013060|publisher=[[ESPN]]|title=Something has to change for No. 18 Texas, Kansas State|accessdate=September 29, 2018|date=September 25, 2018}}</ref>\n\nTexas was the only team to score in the first half of play, with two touchdowns, a field goal, and a safety.  Kansas State had a chance to score a touchdown on the final play of the first half when Alex Delton threw a pass to Adam Harter that was dropped in the end zone.  The score at the half was Texas 19, Kansas State 0.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kansas.com/sports/college/big-12/kansas-state/article219245450.html#storylink=cpy|accessdate=September 29, 2018|date=September 29, 2018|publisher=[[Wichita Eagle]]|title=Skylar Thompson\u2019s comeback attempt falls short as Texas beats K-State 19-14|first=Kellis|last=Robinett}}</ref>\n\nKansas State fared better in the second half, holding Texas scoreless and replacing Alex Delton with Skylar Thompson.  Thompson led Kansas State to score two touchdowns in the second half with 14 points.  In the end, Texas held the lead with a final score of 19-14.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://themercury.com/k_state_sports/thompson-gets-offense-going-in-second-half-in-loss-to/article_9a00e094-b559-507e-b01b-6b7f526204f1.html|title=Thompson gets offense going in second half in loss to No. 18 Texas |first=Greg|last=Woods|publisher=[[Manhattan Mercury]]|accessdate=September 29, 2018|date=September 29, 2018}}</ref>  For the next week Texas plays Oklahoma after stopping the second-half comeback by Kansas State.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sportsday.dallasnews.com/college-sports/texaslonghorns/2018/09/29/national-reaction-texas-win-k-state-longhorns-get-can-handle-wildcats-gritty-win|title=National reaction from Texas' win over K-State: Longhorns get all they can handle from Wildcats in gritty win|accessdate=September 30, 2018|publisher=[[Dallas Morning News]]|date=September 29, 2018|first=Trenton|last=Daeschner}}</ref>\n\n===vs Oklahoma===\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road=No. 7 Sooners\n|R1=7\n|R2=10\n|R3=7\n|R4=21\n|Home= '''No. 19 Longhorns'''\n|H1=10\n|H2=14\n|H3=21\n|H4=3\n}}\n{{see also|2018 Oklahoma Sooners football team|Red River Showdown}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Overall record\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Last meeting\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Result\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 61\u201346\u20135\n| 2017\n| OU, 29\u201324\n|}\nThe 2018 edition of this classic rivalry matchup was pivotal for both the Longhorns and the Sooners, as both had something to prove; OU was playing its first ranked opponent of the season, and Texas was trying to show that it could once again compete with the elite of the NCAA after years of very average performances. This year's game, which ended in a Longhorn victory, was the highest-scoring Red River Showdown game in history, with a combined score of 93. A memorable aspect of this game was Texas' dominance until midway through the fourth quarter, only to eventually surrender a 21-point lead to the Sooners late in the game; Heisman candidate [[Kyler Murray]] put on an incredible performance, showcasing his superior speed and accuracy. This comeback, however, did not come to fruition, as Texas kicker Cameron Dicker made a 40-yard field goal with approximately 9 seconds remaining on the clock to win the game for Texas.\n{{-}}\n\n===Baylor===\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road=Bears\n|R1=7\n|R2=3\n|R3=7\n|R4=0\n|Home='''No. 9 Longhorns'''\n|H1=3\n|H2=20\n|H3=0\n|H4=0\n}}\n{{see also|2018 Baylor Bears football team}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Texas Longhorns|Overall record|Last meeting|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 76\u201326\u20135\n| 2017\n| TEX, 38\u20137\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===at Oklahoma State===\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road=No. 6 Longhorns\n|R1=7\n|R2=7\n|R3=7\n|R4=14\n|Home='''Cowboys'''\n|H1=17\n|H2=14\n|H3=0\n|H4=7\n}}\n{{see also|2018 Oklahoma State Cowboys football team}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Overall record\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Last meeting\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Result\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 24\u20138\n| 2017\n| OKST, 13\u201310\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===West Virginia===\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road='''No. 12 Mountaineers'''\n|R1=10\n|R2=17\n|R3=0\n|R4=15\n|Home=No. 15 Longhorns\n|H1=14\n|H2=14\n|H3=3\n|H4=10\n}}\n{{see also|2018 West Virginia Mountaineers football team}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Texas Longhorns|Overall record|Last meeting|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 3\u20134\n| 2017\n| TEX, 28\u201314\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===at Texas Tech===\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road='''No. 15 Longhorns'''\n|R1=0\n|R2=17\n|R3=10\n|R4=14\n|Home=Red Raiders\n|H1=7\n|H2=3\n|H3=0\n|H4=24\n}}\n{{see also|2018 Texas Tech Red Raiders football team|Texas\u2013Texas Tech football rivalry}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Overall record\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Last meeting\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Result\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 50\u201317\n| 2017\n| TTU, 27\u201323\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===Iowa State===\n{{Linescore Amfootball||Road=No. 16 Cyclones\n|R1=3\n|R2=0\n|R3=0\n|R4=7\n|Home='''No. 15 Longhorns'''\n|H1=7\n|H2=10\n|H3=7\n|H4=0\n}}\n{{see also|2018 Iowa State Cyclones football team}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Texas Longhorns|Overall record|Last meeting|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 13\u20132\n| 2017\n| TEX, 17\u20137\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===at Kansas===\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road='''No. 15 Longhorns'''\n|R1=7\n|R2=0\n|R3=14\n|R4=3\n|Home=Jayhawks\n|H1=0\n|H2=0\n|H3=0\n|H4=17\n}}\n{{see also|2018 Kansas Jayhawks football team}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Overall record\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Last meeting\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Result\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 14\u20133\n| 2017\n| TEX, 42\u201327\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===vs Oklahoma (2018 Big 12 Championship)===\n{{see also|2018 Oklahoma Sooners football team|Red River Showdown|2018 Big 12 Championship Game}}\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road=No. 15 Longhorns\n|R1=7 |R2=7 |R3=13 |R4=0\n|Home='''No. 4 Sooners'''\n|H1=3 |H2=17 |H3=7 |H4=12 \n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Overall record\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Last meeting\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Result\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 62\u201346\u20135\n| 2018\n| TEX, 48\u201345\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===vs Georgia (2019 Sugar Bowl)===\n{{see also|2018 Georgia Bulldogs football team|2019 Sugar Bowl}}\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road='''No. 15 Longhorns'''\n|R1=10 |R2=10 |R3=0 |R4=8\n|Home=No. 5 Bulldogs\n|H1=0 |H2=7 |H3=0 |H4=14\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Overall record\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Last meeting\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"|Result\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 3\u20131\n| 1984\n| UGA, 10\u20139\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n==Rankings==\n{{Further|2018 NCAA Division I FBS football rankings}}\n{{NCAA Division I FBS CFP ranking movements\n| year            = {{2018}}\n| finalpollweek   = -\n| cfpfirstweek    = 9\n| AP_pre          = 23\n| coaches_pre     = 21\n| AP_1            = NR\n| coaches_1       = NR\n| AP_2            = NR\n| coaches_2       = RV\n| AP_3            = RV\n| coaches_3       = RV\n| AP_4            = 18\n| coaches_4       = 22\n| AP_5            = 19\n| coaches_5       = 20\n| AP_6            = 9\n| coaches_6       = 14\n| AP_7            = 7\n| coaches_7       = 8\n| AP_8            = 6\n| coaches_8       = 7\n| AP_9            = 15\n| coaches_9       = 15\n| cfp_9           = 17\n| AP_10           = 15\n| coaches_10      = 19\n| cfp_10          = 19\n| AP_11           = 13\n| coaches_11      = 14\n| cfp_11          = 15\n| AP_12           = 11\n| coaches_12      = 11\n| cfp_12          = 14\n| AP_13           = 9\n| coaches_13      = 9\n| cfp_13          = 14\n| AP_14           = 14\n| coaches_14      = 14\n| cfp_14          = 15\n| AP_15           = 9\n| coaches_15      = 9\n}}\n\n==Players drafted into the NFL==\n{{see also|2019 NFL Draft}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; {{CollegePrimaryStyle|Texas Longhorns|border=0}}\"\n| '''Round''' || '''Pick''' || '''Player''' || '''Position''' || '''NFL Club'''\n|-\n| 5 || 161 || [[Charles Omenihu]] || DE || [[Houston Texans]]\n|-\n| 7 || 217 || [[Kris Boyd (American football)|Kris Boyd]] || CB || [[Minnesota Vikings]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{Texas Longhorns football navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Texas Longhorns Football Team}}\n[[Category:2018 Big 12 Conference football season]]\n[[Category:Sugar Bowl champion seasons|2018]]\n[[Category:Texas Longhorns football seasons|2018]]\n[[Category:2018 in sports in Texas]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n| mode    = football\n| year    = 2018\n| team    = Texas Longhorns\n| logo = Texas Longhorns logo.svg\n| logo_size = 150px\n| conference = Big 12 Conference\n|short_conf   = Big 12\n|CoachRank= 9\n|APRank= 9\n|CFPRank= \n|record= 10\u20134\n|conf_record= 7\u20132\n|head_coach= [[Tom Herman (American football)|Tom Herman]]\n|hc_year= 2nd\n| off_coach = [[Tim Beck (American football, born 1966)|Tim Beck]]\n| oc_year = 2nd\n| cooff_coach1=Herb Hand\n| cooc1_year= 1st\n| off_scheme = [[Spread offense|Spread]]\n| def_coach = [[Todd Orlando]]\n| dc_year = 2nd\n| def_scheme = [[3\u20134 defense|3\u20134]]\n|conf_champ = [[2018 Big 12 Championship Game|Big 12 Championship Game]]\n|conf_champ_result = <br>L 27\u201339 vs. [[2018 Oklahoma Sooners football team|Oklahoma]]\n|captain = Andrew Beck<br>Breckyn Hager<br>Chris Nelson<br>Elijah Rodriguez<br>Anthony Wheeler\n|stadium= [[Darrell K Royal\u2013Texas Memorial Stadium]]<br>(Capacity: 100,119)\n| champion = Sugar Bowl champion\n| bowl = [[2019 Sugar Bowl|Sugar Bowl]]\n| bowl_result =  W 28\u201321 vs. [[2018 Georgia Bulldogs football team|Georgia]]\n|prev_year=|next_year=}}\n{{2018 Big 12 football standings}}\nThe '''2018 Texas Longhorns football team''', known variously as \"Texas\", \"UT\", the \"Longhorns\", or the \"Horns\u201d, represented the [[University of Texas at Austin]] during the [[2018 NCAA Division I FBS football season]]. The Longhorns played their home games at [[Darrell K Royal\u2013Texas Memorial Stadium]] in [[Austin, Texas]], and competed as members of the [[Big 12 Conference]]. They were led by second-year head coach [[Tom Herman (American football)|Tom Herman]].\n\nTexas, coming off a 7\u20136 season in Herman's first year, began the year ranked 23rd in the preseason [[AP Poll]]. In the first game of the year, the Longhorns were upset by [[2018 Maryland Terrapins football team|Maryland]] in a game played at [[FedExField]] in [[Landover, Maryland]]. The team won its next six games, including a dramatic win over No. 7 [[2018 Oklahoma Sooners football team|Oklahoma]] in the 113th [[Red River Showdown]]. The Longhorns rose as high as sixth in the AP Poll, but fell in consecutive weeks to [[2018 Oklahoma State Cowboys football team|Oklahoma State]] and [[2018 West Virginia Mountaineers football team|West Virginia]]. At the end of the regular season, Texas had a record of 7\u20132 in Big 12 play, good for second in the standings and earning them a spot in the [[2018 Big 12 Championship Game|Big 12 Championship Game]] against Oklahoma. The Sooners won the rematch by a score of 39\u201327. Texas was invited to the [[2019 Sugar Bowl|Sugar Bowl]] to play [[Southeastern Conference|SEC]] runner-up No. 5 [[2018 Georgia Bulldogs football team|Georgia]], which Texas won in an upset by a score of 28\u201321. They finished with an overall record of 10\u20134 and were ranked 9th in the final AP Poll, the most wins and highest ranked finish for the school since [[2009 Texas Longhorns football team|2009]].\n\nThe team was led on offense by sophomore quarterback [[Sam Ehlinger]], who finished with 3,292 passing yards, 25 passing touchdowns, and a Big 12-leading 16 rushing touchdowns. His 41 total touchdowns was third in the conference and seventh nationally.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/conferences/big-12/2018.html|title=2018 Big 12 Conference Year Summary|website=Sports-Reference.com|access-date=June 4, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/years/2018.html|title=2018 College Football Year Sumary|website=Sports-Reference.com|access-date=June 4, 2019}}</ref> Wide receiver [[Lil'Jordan Humphrey]] led the team with 1,176 receiving yards. On defense, the team had three [[2018 All-Big 12 Conference football team|first-team all-conference]] members in defensive lineman [[Charles Omenihu]] and defensive backs [[Kris Boyd (American football)|Kris Boyd]] and [[Caden Sterns]].\n\n==Previous season==\nThe Longhorns finished the [[2017 Texas Longhorns football team|2017 season]] 7\u20136, 5\u20134 in Big 12 play to finish in four-way tie for fourth place. They were invited to the [[2017 Texas Bowl|Texas Bowl]] where they defeated [[2017 Missouri Tigers football team|Missouri]].\n\n==Preseason==\n===Award watch lists===\n<small>Listed in the order that they were released</small>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Texas Longhorns|Award|Player|Position|Year}}\n|-\n|[[Rimington Trophy]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Rimington Trophy Press Release|url=http://www.rimingtontrophy.com/news/?article_id=100|date=May 30, 2018|accessdate=July 14, 2018}}</ref>\n|Zach Shackelford\n|C\n|JR\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Chuck Bednarik Award]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.maxwellfootballclub.org/2018-maxwell-bednarik-watch-list/|title=2018 Bednarik Award Watch List - Maxwell Football Club|date=2018-07-16|work=Maxwell Football Club|access-date=2018-07-17|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|Breckyn Hager\n|DE\n|SR\n|-\n|Gary Johnson\n|LB\n|SR\n|-\n|[[Fred Biletnikoff Award]]<ref>{{cite web|title=2018 Biletnikoff Award Watch List|url=http://biletnikoffaward.com/2018-biletnikoff-award-watch-list|date=July 19, 2018|accessdate=July 19, 2018}}</ref>\n|[[Collin Johnson]]\n|WR\n|JR\n|-\n|[[John Mackey Award]]<ref>{{cite web|title=2018 John Mackey Award Preseason Watch List Released|url=http://w